Mass . to pay off Middlesex debt today - report . The Massachusetts Office of Administration and Finance will pay $ 11 . 9 billion in overdue bonds and other debts due today , the Boston Herald reported Thursday . Mass . Governor William Weld signed legislation last week eliminating Middlesex County , which defaulted on a bond payment earlier this year . The state Senate has estimated it would cost about $ 25 million to cover Middlesex County debts , but Leslie Kirwan , the head of the state Office of Administration and Finance , told the Herald the actual cost will likely be lower . ( ( Boston bureau , ( 617 ) 367 - 4106 ) ) 
